messages.messageBody:
Thank you Barb, my biggest thing is that I'm just plain scared to drive with
4 kids all by myself. Plus I don't like to drive and get sleepy headed
after 3-4 hours. I get too many what-if's going on in my head and talk
myself out of it, but I haven't wanted to travel to a conference this much
before either..lol. So we will see. Hopefully hubby can come with me and I
won't have to worry about driving, but, the more I read here, the more I
want to go, and I know the kids would love it. We got a tv last big trip
(hubby with us) and they watched videos too, they loved it...smoothest trip
we ever had. When's the deadline for the family rate?

-------------------------
Tammy, I've done a lot of travel with just me and my boys. Book on tape,
sing-a-longs, snacks, and a few small new Dollar Store toys can make a trip
a lot easier on my guys when they were little. We've seen and done a lot.
Need ideas just ask. :-)
Barb E
